Media Queries:

    1.      Helps create a responsive website.

    2.      Source-     medium.com

    3.      Media features- width (of viewport), there are manymore features of viewport that could be changed or modified accordingly using CSS.

                @media(width: 400px) {
                    div{
                        background-color: red;
                    }
                }

                --> Most commonly used:
                
                    @media (min-width: 400px){
                        div{
                            background-color: red;
                        }
                    }

                    @media (max-width){
                        background-color: orange;
                    }

                --> Responsiveness is commonly used in navbar.
                --> We can hide or show an html element according to the responsiveness.

                --> Ranging the responsiveness using 'and'.
                        @media (min-width: 200px) and (max-width: 800px){
                            h1{
                                something;
                            }

                            div{
                                something;
                            }
                        }

                --> Orientation of Viewport:    landscape or portrait
                        @media (orientation: landscape){
                            div{
                                something;
                            }
                        }